    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but \"small moments\" feel so hollow when you look at the actual scale of things. if the end result is always absolute nothingness, then all the striving for \"impact\" or \"beauty\" is just a temporary distraction from the fact that nothing lasts. doesn't it feel a bit delusional to try and find meaning in a system that is inherently designed to erase everything?",
